com.worldpay

Class Worldpay

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.worldpay.Worldpay

  • public class Worldpay
extends java.lang.Object
    Worldpay main class based on singleton pattern.

    Developer can access the instance of the library using getInstance() .

    Settings

    It is mandatory to set the client key using setClientKey(String). Other possible settings are :
    • Set reusable token mode using setReusable(boolean) in order to reuse token.
    • Enable / disable debugging mode using setDebug(boolean) or setDebug(boolean, String).

    Usage

      Steps:
    1. Set your client key :
       Worldpay.getInstance().setClientKey(YOUR_CLIENT_KEY);
    2. Create a card and set data.
       Card card = new Card();
 card.setHolderName(name).setCardNumber(cNumber).setCvc(cvc).setExpiryYear(expYear).setExpriryMonth(expMonth);
    3. Validate the card :
       CardValidationError validate = card.validate();
 
 if (validate != null && validate.hasErrors()) {
        //validation errors exist
 } else {
        //everything is ok, you can continue
 }
      If validation errors exist, check CardValidationError class for more information.
    4. Create and execute createTokenAsyncTask(Context, Card, WorldpayResponse) in order to create an AsyncTask, which executes the transaction with Worldpay and returns the response asynchronously to a callback interface.

      Implement WorldpayResponse interface, to handle response from the Worldpay. 
       AsyncTask<Void, Void, ServerResponse> createTokenAsyncTask = worldpay.createTokenAsyncTask(this, card, new WorldpayResponse() {
 
        @Override
        public void onSuccess(ResponseCard responseCard) {
                DebugLogger.d("# onSuccess : " + responseCard);
        }
 
        @Override
        public void onResponseError(ResponseError responseError) {
                DebugLogger.d("# onResponseError: " + responseError.getMessage());
        }
 
        @Override
        public void onError(WorldpayError worldpayError) {
                DebugLogger.d("# onError: " + worldpayError.getMessage());
        }
 
 });
    See Also:
    Card, CardValidationError, WorldpayResponse, ResponseCard, ResponseError, WorldpayError
